[
    {
        "content": "<p>Would somebody be able to point me to where x86 return ABI is figured out, specifically on Windows? I assume it has to be somewhere here but I can't find it <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/90ae123dc4f1c4d2e8c3bffaa61094d9a970d650/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/abi.rs\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/90ae123dc4f1c4d2e8c3bffaa61094d9a970d650/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/abi.rs</a></p>",
        "id": 609072662,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783539345
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>f129 is currently returned in xmm0 but LLVM recently changed to return indirectly (matching GCC) so I'm looking to do the same update here</p>",
        "id": 609072797,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783539402
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think you'll want code <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/90ae123dc4f1c4d2e8c3bffaa61094d9a970d650/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/abi.rs#L219-L255\">somewhere around here perhaps</a> (in that <code>abi.rs</code> file)</p>",
        "id": 609076013,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1783540521
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That and the block below it seem to only be for argument handling (at least, based on <code>ArgsOrRets</code>)</p>",
        "id": 609077141,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783540889
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was kind of trying to trace where the <code>i128</code> handling would be since that's similar-ish, returning in registers on most platforms but xmm on Windows. But I couldn't seem to find it anywhere</p>",
        "id": 609077256,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783540929
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/90ae123dc4f1c4d2e8c3bffaa61094d9a970d650/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/abi.rs#L199-L207\">if above that</a> I know I've seen before in terms of handling returns-of-i128, but I'm not immediately seeing where it connects to regalloc and such</p>",
        "id": 609078379,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1783541334
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it might be <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/90ae123dc4f1c4d2e8c3bffaa61094d9a970d650/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/abi.rs#L314\">this loop though</a> where <code>reg_tys</code> will have two elements for i64 I believe</p>",
        "id": 609078521,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1783541384
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hm hm <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/260f9d4bf7c37f98ab8234231b17bc9158eaaaca/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/inst/mod.rs#L1410-L1432\"><code>rc_for_type</code></a> doesn't do any special handling for <code>i128</code> and I don't see anything specific for Windows in that loop. Maybe clif doesn't actually have specific handling for windows i128 and the frontend handles that instead?</p>",
        "id": 609081178,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783542308
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Since you're around, how do you get rustc to emit the .clif? I thought <code>--emit=clif</code> worked but it seems it doesn't</p>",
        "id": 609081404,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783542363
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wouldn't be surprised yeah if it's a frontend thing, I don't think we have native tests in cranelift itself about Rust code using a plain <code>extern \"C\"</code> to call an i128-returning function</p>",
        "id": 609081484,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1783542394
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for rustc emitting clif I'd ask bjorn3, I'm not sure myself</p>",
        "id": 609081508,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1783542404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"264278\">@bjorn3</span> do you happen to know more about how/where this works?</p>",
        "id": 609082273,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783542576
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>--emit=llvm-ir should work</p>",
        "id": 609082472,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1783542631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, it errors but still creates the files</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">RUSTFLAGS</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s\">\"-Zcodegen-backend=cranelift\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rustc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">emit</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">llvm</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">ir</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">Compiling</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">f128</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"n\">projects</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">scratch</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">f128</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">could</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">copy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/Users/tmgross/Documents/projects/scratch/clif-f128/target/debug/deps/clif_f128-d2d7b61ef0548f3f.edabakgdnj4dr38hhli25hfbo.0k4dnte.rcgu.ll\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/Users/tmgross/Documents/projects/scratch/clif-f128/target/debug/deps/clif_f128-d2d7b61ef0548f3f.ll\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">No</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">such</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">directory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">os</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">could</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compile</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">f128</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">due</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">previous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span>\n<span class=\"n\">tmgross</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"n\">quince</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">f128</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span>\n<span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">debug</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">deps</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">clif_f128</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">d2d7b61ef0548f3f</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">/</span>\n<span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">debug</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">deps</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">clif_f128</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">d2d7b61ef0548f3f</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pass_f128</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">opt</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span>\n<span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">debug</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">deps</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">clif_f128</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">d2d7b61ef0548f3f</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">pass_f128</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">unopt</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span>\n<span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">debug</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">deps</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">clif_f128</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">d2d7b61ef0548f3f</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">ret_f128</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">opt</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span>\n<span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">debug</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">deps</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">clif_f128</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">d2d7b61ef0548f3f</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">ret_f128</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">unopt</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clif</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 609082735,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783542704
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The windows i128 abi is implemented in rustc (through abi adjustments) and (for libcalls) in cg_clif (eg <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rustc_codegen_cranelift/blob/5bbb9e4f6618aa7c32bde230875fa36608e60bdf/src/abi/mod.rs#L164\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rustc_codegen_cranelift/blob/5bbb9e4f6618aa7c32bde230875fa36608e60bdf/src/abi/mod.rs#L164</a>)</p>",
        "id": 609082913,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1783542774
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the rustc side: <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/7ef36edc23ac10760eb9f097d32edbab2e1e8928/compiler/rustc_target/src/callconv/x86_win64.rs#L21\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/7ef36edc23ac10760eb9f097d32edbab2e1e8928/compiler/rustc_target/src/callconv/x86_win64.rs#L21</a></p>",
        "id": 609083030,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1783542819
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the copy error is because cg_ssa expects a single .ll file to be generated, while cg_clif produces a directory of files.</p>",
        "id": 609083164,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1783542880
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Doesn't cranelift itself need knowledge of the ABI? For knowing how to emit libcalls</p>",
        "id": 609083168,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783542883
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(I'm looking at this all because of <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/158918\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/158918</a>)</p>",
        "id": 609083199,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783542892
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>all 128bit libcalls are emitted as regular calls on the cg_clif side. Cranelift itself doesn't have libcalls for 128bit operations.</p>",
        "id": 609083274,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1783542926
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you could adjust the cg_clif code i linked to apply for f128 in addition to i128. together with the abi adjustment change you already do in your PR that should be enough to make it work.</p>",
        "id": 609083532,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1783543023
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah - so e.g. <code>f128 * f128</code> is changed to <code>__multf2</code> in the rustc backend before even hitting cranelift's codegen?</p>",
        "id": 609083592,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783543049
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>__multif3, but yes: <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rustc_codegen_cranelift/blob/5bbb9e4f6618aa7c32bde230875fa36608e60bdf/src/codegen_f16_f128.rs#L137\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rustc_codegen_cranelift/blob/5bbb9e4f6618aa7c32bde230875fa36608e60bdf/src/codegen_f16_f128.rs#L137</a></p>",
        "id": 609083819,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1783543138
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Alright, that all makes a lot more sense. Thanks for the help clearing this up</p>",
        "id": 609083952,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1783543194
    }
]